Thuirt Alasdair MacFhionghuin gu bheil seirbheis eile ga toirt air falbh bho sgìre air an tuath. Tha Seirbheis Cùirt na h-Alba airson deich cùirtean siorraim a dhùnadh agus seachd cùirtean maoir cheartais, is iad ag ràdh gun tuit am buidseat 20% ro 2015.

The Trees for Life vision is of a revitalised wild forest in the Scottish Highlands, providing space for wildlife to flourish and communities to thrive. Ar N-Aisling Tha Trees for Life a coimhead air adhart gu coilltean ùr ‘s fiadhaich air feadh a’ Ghàidhealtachd – àite nàdarrach airson fiadh-bheatha agus coimhearsnachdan a’ shoirbhich. The Trees for Life mission is to rewild the Scottish Highlands by enabling the restoration of the globally unique Caledonian Forest which once covered much of Scotland. Integral to our success is the involvement of people. Ar N-Aithris ruin Tha Trees for Life ag obair cruaidh a cur ath-fhiadhachadh air adhart ann a’ Ghàidhealtachd, agus a a’ toirt stiùireadh seachad mar thaic dhan a choille Cailleannach. Tha coimhearsnachdan agus ranntannan gu math cuideamach airson an obair seo.
